'''Hallucigenia''' is a {{Rarity|Rare}} fish found in the [[Ancient Isle]].

== Description ==
{{Description|The Hallucigenia is an elongated, worm-like creature with spiney appendages throughout its body. They went extinct around 485 million years ago, at the end of the Ordovician period. They are quite low on the food chain, primarily feeding on small microorganisms.|Bestiary Entry}}

